{{Quote|The Januul and the Borokii have been at odds for as long as anyone can remember. Who should have preeminence among the Alwari has been cause for fighting for hundreds of years.|[[Bayaar]], to the Jedi and their companions|<ref name="The Approaching Storm">''[[The Approaching Storm]]''</ref>}}
The '''Borokii''' were considered the most powerful overclan of the [[Alwari]] nomad tribes of [[Ansion/Legends|Ansion]]. Maintaining their livelihoods within the transitory bounds of a portable [[Borokii camp|camp]], they were armed with traditional [[Long knife|long knives]] and [[Malarian]] [[laser pistol]]s and had herds of [[surepp]].

The Borokii were ruled by a [[Borokii Council of Elders|Council of Elders]] and contained twelve sub-clans, including the most preeminent among them, the [[Situng Borokii]]. Their traditional enemies were the [[Januul]]; as of [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], they had clashed for centuries over which tribe should be senior among the Alwari. At the time of the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Border dispute on Ansion/Legends|mission to Ansion]], the Borokii were the ruling overclan of the Alwari tribes.

